We want you to feel inspired, creatively refreshed and brimming with ideas. We have a 'floral crown' and 'bangle me baby' workshop coming up as part of #MSFW on Sunday 31 August. So make a commitment to learn at least one new skill before the year is over. Your soul will thank you for it.

Tags: create, workshop, make, flowers, msfw, creative
Caption: It's contagious you know. Colour. Arousing your senses. Creating with your own two hands. Each participant presented with the same tools and supplies, yet somehow managing to create different and equally beautiful results. Is such an inspiring thing to watch unfold. And at the end, big, honest heart-warming smiles all around. This, is why we do what we do. So that you guys can walk away full of creative, happy hearts. Full of inspiration. Full of ideas. And for a moment our faith in all that is good and beautiful and happy is restored. Tags: styleadvice, layering, style, spring, melbourne, sydney, personalshopping, msfw
Caption:
|| LAYERS|| A perfectly layered look will compliment your curves and create the illusion of a more proportional silhouette. Layering can add texture, volume and depth to your outfit. Many women are afraid to layer their clothes for fear of looking bigger than they actually are. It couldn't be further from the truth, if done right. TIPS: 1. Start with a basic, lightweight top. I suggest a solid colour, something neutral, or striped.
2. Keep the under-layers more fitted to keep your shape looking slim. 3. Length and proportion is key when layering. 4. Play with texture. Itâ€™s best to incorporate a mix of materials when styling a layered look. If you use all of the same fabrics, youâ€™re look could make you appear heavier then you are. x #styleadvice #layering #msfw #personalshopping #melbourne #sydney #spring #style

Caption: It's always nice to see a surprise performance right where you happen to be. This time it's a drum performance at the State Library of Victoria (SLV), right in the middle of La Trobe Reading Room. It's a performance of art and theatre, to celebrate Liberty of the Press, as part of Melbourne Spring Fashion Week. What's more impressive is how the library staff very considerately offered earplugs to everyone there, to people whom might not want to be disturbed. Loving you more and more each day, SLV. ??

Buon Appetito! These were ridiculously EASY TO MAKE!! so light, fluffy and most of all delicious. Recipe Deets?? Gnocchi: 1x375g tub ricotta (drained) 3/4 cup plain flour, 3/4 cup Parmigiano regiano cheese, 1/4 cup chopped chives. Salt & pepper to taste. Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl until well combined. Tear a lemon sized ball off the mixture and roll out into a long skinny tube shape. Cut into 3-5cm pieces and roll onto gnocchi board or back of a fork to make grooves. Set aside or freeze until you want to cook them. ( In a medium sized saucepan fill with water and salt, once it comes to boil place gnocchi in and cook for around 3-4 mins) you know they are cooked when they all float up to the surface. Remove with slotted spoon. Serve with sauce of your choice. ?? Enjoy Xxx

Tags: emporium, mimco, spring, smilingmoments, roses, smallactsofkindness, inspiration, msfw, scents, orchids
Caption:
Day 2: A day of sightseeing, wrong turns, discoveries and smiling moments. 
Working the floral runway led to chocolate from a handsome Mimco guy who liked my pentagram necklace and shared my love of flowers, and to gifting the biggest most beautiful flower I had saved to a darling 5 year old. From her grin I could tell I'd made her night. Amidst the sweet scent a strange moment occurred when a man stopped me claiming to be able to tell me my future simply from my star sign. Despite my scepticism many things resonated with me, giving me reassurance and inspiration to continue toward my goals. Free nail art from a pop up salon in the Emporium was simply the cherry to my wonderful day.
